         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Botanic Garden ¶ Brisbane 27 December 1872 ¶ Dear Baron Von Mueller ¶  ¶ Your favor of the 12 inst ¶  safe to hand and I have much pleasure in stating that the Doryanthus ¶  Palmeri was first noticed ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.12.27</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Walter Hill</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M10, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens, Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">MS found with a specimen of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Doryanthes palmeri</seg> (MEL 2270084), annotated by Hill: 'Oct 1870, W. Hill'.</p>
               </note>Botanic Garden</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Brisbane 27 December 1872</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Dear Baron Von Mueller</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your favor of the 12 inst<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter not found.</p>
               </note> safe to hand and I have much pleasure in stating that the Doryanthus<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Doryanthes</seg>.</p>
               </note> Palmeri was first noticed by me growing upon Mount Spicer near Cunningham Gap<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Qld.</p>
               </note> some 17 year ago at the time in the month of July it was not in flower and I set it down for D. excelsa so much did it resemble it in its habitate about 7 year after I was passing that way and brought several plants with me for the Garden and the first flowered in 1870. The flower stem was erect and rose to the height of 12 feet the flower[ing] part was 3 feet 6 inch I have paid a visit twice this season for the purpose of obtaining seeds but as yet have failed none of it having become ripe</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The locality that Hartman<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Carl Hartmann.</p>
               </note> sent you the specimen of is about 20 miles from where I found it. Mr Guilfoyle of the Exot[ic] Nursery says it is upon the dividing range between Queenslan[d] and New South Wales.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I named [it]<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> in Honor of the Honorable The Colonial Secretary (A. H. Palmer) of Queensland I think it is the finest plant I have seen of the order it belongs to. A fine figure of it was sent to Dr Hooker of Kew. The drawing was made by a Mr Scott of Sydney — the Dr says it is a superb plant.<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">In the text accompanying an illustration of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">D. palmeri</seg> (J. Hooker (1865-1904), vol. 109, tab. 6665), Joseph Hooker states that the drawing was made by 'Miss Scott', as does Bentham (1863-78), vol. 6, p. 453.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I also discovered a white variety of Doryanth. Excelsa growing upon Mount Lindsay.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Qld.</p>
               </note> It flowered last year and was much admired.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I enclose what I take to be a new orchid perhaps a <name key="Gooderia">Gooderia</name>.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Goodyera</seg>?</p>
               </note> I could not find any of it in flower — the leaves has a white stripe up the centere.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>In another letter I send you some specimen of <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name> &amp; othe[r] and should feel much indepted to you to put me [ryght] in their names some of the <name key="Acacia">Acacia</name> is handsome trees I hope you will be able to make them all out.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I start tomorrow to the Rosewood Scrub and will bring you some others that I think I will find. have you come across the name of the Palm yet. It is in fine fruit with us — trusting to hear from you soon &amp;c</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">I am</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>yours truly</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva, Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Walter Hill</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
